The paper focuses on Requirements Engineering (RE) processes, which is a subfield of Software Engineering (SE). Therefore, cs.SE is the most likely category. The paper also deals with project parameters and execution strategies, which are related to the management and control of software development projects, making cs.CY (Control and Systems) a likely category as well. The use of content analysis and cluster analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subcategories of cs.SD (Software Development) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper mentions the importance of tailoring the RE process to individual project characteristics, which is related to Human-Computer Interaction (HCI), making cs.HC a possible category as well.
